icide and death and disproves the long-held belief that Mexicans possess a cavalier attitude toward suffering.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aDeathxSocial aspectszMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMurderzMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aSuicidezMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520964532.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles